Exercise 0.6:
- Create a diagram depicting the situation where the user creates a new note using the single-page version of the app.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser->>server: submits the form without an action or a method.
    activate server
    note right of browser: the new request has the note's content as json data.
    server-->>browser: Process GET request, returns HTML, CSS and executes JavaScript file.
    deactivate server
    Note right of browser: The JavaScript file will be crucial to fetch the json data later.
    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the css file
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser starts executing the JavaScript code that fetches the JSON from the server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: [{ "content": "HTML is easy", "date": "2023-1-1" }, ... ]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function that renders the notes
```
